title: Grateful Dead Live at Philadelphia Civic Center on 1984-04-21
lineage: Dat (Sony R500) > Tascam DA-3000 > Adobe Audition CC 2015 >Samplitude Pro X3 Suite > FLAC/
description:
Set 1

Alabama Getaway-> Promised Land, Friend Of The Devil, Me & My Uncle, Mexicali Blues, West L.A. Fadeaway, Minglewood Blues, Tennessee Jed, Looks Like Rain-> Deal

Set 2

Help On The Way-> Slipknot!-> Franklin's Tower-> Playin' In The Band-> China Doll-> Don't Need Love-> Drums-> Wharf Rat-> Throwing Stones-> Not Fade Away, E: Brokedown Palace

Thank U so Much Bigfoot, I mean Jerry so me sitting here I pull this show up and I'mlike I know there is no soundboard BUT THERE IT IS! Also I saw Bigfoot at Holiday Inn last night and I swear she looked like Jerry......
 Thanks, I always thought this one was good. I went to 4/20 with Mom and Dad, only show they ever saw.  I used to have an audience tape we made where u could hear them talking.....Thanks for seeing our plea for the SBD and here it is...............I needed some good news. Sadly I went to this with friends who are gone one is a Trump Racist idiot and the other moved far away...c and m where r u? How can I rate a show I had a good time at?

Trippy fun at UPenn This was like having a second spring break at UPenn (though I attended Temple U.). The only time I was able to walk to a show. Cavernous Civic Center didn't make for spectacular sound but Mr. Miller's SBD is nothing less than superb. Great weather, too. After-party in the Quad was an all-nighter. Notice the Other One teases in Space before moving into Wharf Rat territory.
